cs.MM, cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.HC 

This paper involves the use of multimodal representations from videos, which suggests that it could belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) or Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of textual models suggests that it could also belong to the Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) sub-category. The use of SVM for fusion of multimodal signals suggests that it could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, the focus on emotion recognition suggests that it could also belong to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category.
